\cb2 Arb . [ To GLADIATORS , R. H. corner . How now , ye loitering knaves ? why throng ye thus the public streets ? Ye precious slaves , who sell your blood for gold , and barter groans for hire , home to your lanista , and strain the strength ye boast of - away . Think you , the palm crown and purse of gold are to be won by basking in the sunbeams ? the tigers only prowl by night . Ye human tigers , hence . [ Exit GLADIATORS , R. H. - To the NOBLES ] Nobles of Pompeii , ye grace your rank . [ To GLAUCUS . ] Athenian Glaucus , I greet you as the champion of a slave- it is a noble office .\cb1 \
