\cb2 Arb . Fools , dupes , madmen that you are , whether in business or in pleasure , ye are equally the slaves of the passion ye should rule ; plod on , plod on your petty thirst for power , your servile mummery all pro- voke alike my laughter and my scorn . [ TO CALENUS , who comes down R. H. ] Harkee , Calenus , that shallow fool is in my way .\cb1 \
