\cb2 Lydon . Sporus , we fight unto the death ; yon blessed sun will shed his rays on one of us no more - give me your hand , and may the gods have mercy on him that falls !\cb1 \
\cb2 Spo . Humph ! there's little need of mercy , when a man is once dead ; however , there's my hand - I'd sooner wound than kill thee .\cb1 \
\cb2 [ Drum and trumpet - They fight - SPORUS falls , and LYDON places his foot on him , and holds him down .\cb1 \
\cb2 Lydon . Show me some sign of mercy ! take not the life ye never can recall ! -Will no one speak ? -All hard and wolfish ! Then die ! [ He stabs him . ] But not on my head be thy blood - my father's freedom , it was\cb1 \
